That's true. `PyDict_GetItemRef` raises an exception on error. What would you prefer we do in this case? One option would be:

```cpp
#if CYTHON_AVOID_UNSAFE_BORROWED_REFERENCES && __PYX_LIMITED_VERSION_HEX > 0x030d00b1
int res = PyDict_GetItemRef(tuple_dedup_map, varnames_tuple, &varnames_tuple_dedup);
if (res == -1) goto done;
if (res == 0) {
#else
varnames_tuple_dedup = PyDict_GetItem(tuple_dedup_map, varnames_tuple);
if (!varnames_tuple_dedup) {
#endif
```

